==English==
===Etymology===
[[blend|Blend]] of [[trust fund]] and [[Rastafarian]]
[[Category:Portmanteaus]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A derogatory portmanteau made up from the words ''trust fund'' and ''Rastafarian''. It is used to degrade some white people who allegedly adopt the manners of [[Rastafari]]; in other circumstances they might be called ''[[wigger]]s''. They are people, often young to middle-aged, who are said to fuse the fashion sensibilities of a hippie with those of a Rastafarian. They are often assumed by their detractors to live an unemployed, shiftless life of hedonism based on an unlimited amount of funds (a trust fund); very similar propaganda against Christians was prevalent in the decaying days of the pagan Roman Empire when it was in its most jaded throes. 

